101. Multithreading
A thread is the smallest unit of execution.
Multithreading is a technique where multiple threads run within the same process to perform tasks concurrently.
import threading
def task():
    print("Task Running")
t1 = threading.Thread(target=task)
t1.start()
t1.join()

102. GIL (Global Interpreter Lock)
GIL is a lock in CPython that allows only one thread to execute Python bytecode at a time.
Python is a programming language specification (the blueprint)
CPython is a specific software program (the official interpreter) that runs that code.

103. Multiprocessing
process - is an independent, running instance of a program that has its own fully isolated memory space, system resources, and dedicated Python interpreter
Multiprocessing is the use of two or more physical CPUs (or processor cores) within a single computer system to execute multiple tasks simultaneously.
from multiprocessing import Process
def task():
    print("Running")
p = Process(target=task)
p.start()
p.join()

