114. Monkey patching
Monkey patching is the practice of dynamically modifying classes or functions during runtime.

class Monkey:                   # 1. Define a class with an original method
    def behavior(self):
        return "Eating a banana"

def patched_behavior(self):    # 2. Define a new function with the desired behavior
    return "Playing the drums!

Monkey.behavior = patched_behavior  # 3. Apply the monkey patch at runtime

m = Monkey()            # 4. Test the modification
print(m.behavior()) #"Playing the drums!"


